<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="plain-adj">plain <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /pleɪn/    美 /pleɪn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-clear-obvious">1.★ <strong>清楚的；明白的；易懂的 (clear / obvious)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a plain fact 
明显的事实</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The story is written <strong>in plain English</strong>. 
故事用简单易懂的英语写成。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>简朴的；简单的；单色的</strong></h4>
<p>without anything added or without decoration：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a plain but elegant dress 
朴素淡雅的连衣裙</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>plain yoghurt 
原味酸奶</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The bike is in <strong>plain black</strong> and easy to ride.
这辆自行车是纯黑色的，非常好骑。</p><footer>2012 重庆书面表达</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>平常的；相貌平平的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a policeman in plain clothes 
便衣警察</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Her face is plain, but she has a nice smile! 
她长相普通，但笑容很甜美！</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>坦白的；直率的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Let us be plain with you.
我们坦白对你说吧。</p></div></div>